You can create a basic "Hello World" console application in C# using Visual Studio or any other IDE that supports C#. 

Here's the simple C# code to print "Hello World":

```csharp
using System;

class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        Console.WriteLine("Hello World!");
    }
}
```

Steps to create a console application in Visual Studio:

1. Open Visual Studio.
2. Click `File -> New -> Project`.
3. In the new project dialog, select `Console App (.NET Core)` or `Console App (.NET Framework)` based on your .NET version.
4. Name the project and set the location, then click `OK`.
5. Replace the existing code with the "Hello World" code above.
6. Run the program by pressing `F5` or `Debug -> Start Debugging`. 

Your console should output `Hello World!`.